    takeaways: ['The real barriers to AI adoption are cultural and organisational, not technical', 'Fear among end users of job loss or being judged must be addressed directly, not mandated away', 'Leadership ambivalence is lethal: if leaders do not visibly use AI, neither will their teams', 'Governance gaps (no policy on AI review or escalation) must be resolved before deployment', 'Data literacy investment is a prerequisite for adoption not a nice-to-have after go-live'],
